&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role follows a &lt;strong&gt;3rd &lt;/strong&gt;shift schedule, working from&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;9:30 PM to 6:30 AM&lt;/strong&gt;, with designated days off on &lt;strong&gt;Saturday &amp;amp; Sunday.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Tempo FSQA Supervisor is responsible for driving the food safety and quality control shift functions within Tempo. The role includes a combination of supervision and active participation in the tasks to ensure that all products are safe, consistent, of the highest quality, and meet all requirements.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Detailed Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Reporting &amp;amp; Planning&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assign daily and weekly responsibilities for RTH FSQA Techs and Sanitors, making sure there are appropriate resources to cover all activities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist FSQA RTH Superintendent with development of daily, weekly, monthly, quarterly &amp;amp; annual schedules.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create FSQA Supervisor Recap; document any issues and work with the FSQA RTH Superintendent for resolution&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be aware &amp;amp; proactive on shift metric reporting, understanding report outs &amp;amp; working on plans for improvement.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Quality Control:&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee RTH FSQA functions for all process steps while working closely with production to help monitor and resolve any issues&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support communications with Production Management regarding any process that does not meet the standard requirements, and work together with necessary parties (e.g., Production Management, Production Team Leads, Production Associates, Maintenance, FSQA Managers and FSQA Associates) to resolve issues&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct GMP audits and notify production management of violations; work with Production to resolve any issue&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Food Safety:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

