&lt;p&gt;The Warehouse Supervisor is responsible for overseeing the warehouse team for their shift, ensuring that each required task is executed and conducted properly and safely.&amp;nbsp; The Warehouse Supervisor is also responsible for anticipating and troubleshooting issues as they arise and managing the performance of warehouse leads and associates on their shift with little guidance; using all information available and collaborating with other stakeholders as needed.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Detailed Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Supervision of Core Warehouse Functions:&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Warehouse Supervisor must demonstrate proficiency in all warehouse functions and processes and ensures compliance with standard procedures on a daily basis. The Warehouse Supervisor is accountable for maintaining the layout and organization of all warehouse spaces and ensuring warehouse team is creating and promoting a safe workplace.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Receiving:&lt;/em&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Works with leads, receivers, and warehouse associates to monitor receiving activities to ensure accuracy, integrity of product and dock maintenance are all kept up to company standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensures issues with facility spaces or powered industrial trucks are escalated to Maintenance team via established reporting systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Responsible for WMS compliance of team at receipt through the putaway to storage process.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensures all receiving processes are completed in accordance with SOP. Must be able to adapt plans and communicate effectively to the team ad hoc changes or directives that are not outlined in an SOP.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
